      "name": "AWS EKS - Containers memory utilization >80%",
      "description": "This alert triggers when the average memory utilization of containers in an Amazon EKS cluster exceeds 80%. High memory utilization can lead to container performance issues or even crashes if it reaches critical levels.\n\nCustomization Guidance:\n\nThreshold: The alert is set to trigger at 80% memory utilization. Adjust this threshold based on your environment's tolerance for high memory usage.\n\nCluster Specificity: Customize the alert for different clusters based on their criticality and expected memory consumption.\n\nNotification Frequency: Ensure timely notifications to prevent container failures due to memory exhaustion.\n\nAction: Monitor container performance, scale resources if necessary, and optimize container memory usage.",
      "enabled": false,
      "priority": "ALERT_DEF_PRIORITY_P1",
      "type": "ALERT_DEF_TYPE_METRIC_THRESHOLD",
      "groupByKeys": [
        "ClusterName",
        "cloud_account_id",
        "cloud_region"
      ],
      "incidentsSettings": {
        "notifyOn": "NOTIFY_ON_TRIGGERED_ONLY_UNSPECIFIED",
        "minutes": 1
      },
      "notificationGroup": {
